Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori is due to pay a  visit to Japan June 5-8 before a formal visit to China, foreigm ministry  sources said Friday.
It will be the fifth visit by Fujimori, the son of Japanese immigrants in  Peru who was elected president in 1990, including one he made before his  inauguration, they said.
The Peruvian president is scheduled to attend a dinner hosted by Prime  Minister Tsutomu Hata and meet Emperor Akihito during his stay, the officials  said.
The Japanese prime minister is expected to voice support for Peru's reform  efforts, while Fujimori is likely to call for more Japanese investment.
Fujimori will be accompanied by Efrain Goldenberg, foreign minister and  president of the Council of Ministers.
Fujimori last visited Japan in May last year.
